    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-12-08</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-12-21T23:58:25Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Protecting the American Taxpayer and Medicare Act</b></p> <p>This bill makes several budgetary and technical changes, particularly in relation to Medicare. </p> <p>Specifically, the bill continues to exempt Medicare from sequestration until March 31, 2022. (Sequestration is a process of automatic, usually across-the-board spending reductions under which budgetary resources are permanently cancelled to enforce specific budget policy goals.)</p> <p>Additionally, the bill (1) temporarily extends other provisions under Medicare, including a payment increase under the physician fee schedule; and (2) requires any debits recorded for FY2022 on the statutory pay-as-you-go (PAYGO) scorecards to be deducted from the scorecards for 2022 and added to the scorecards for 2023.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
